summary: This document is an account transfer form detailing the transfer of assets from one financial institution to another. It includes sections for receiving and delivering firm information, account types, and transfer types. Notably, it mentions JP Morgan as the delivering firm and includes various account types and transfer options.
keyFacts: The document is an account transfer form.
JP Morgan is identified as the delivering firm.
The form includes various account types such as retirement accounts and corporate accounts.
It outlines options for transferring assets, including liquidation and in-kind transfers.
The document is marked as confidential under federal rules.
